cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with information extraction from text, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and hence, is likely to be classified under cs.CL. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an end-to-end model based on pointer networks, which is a machine learning technique. Hence, it is likely to be classified under cs.LG. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - Information extraction is a subfield of AI, and the paper proposes a novel approach to address this problem. Hence, it is likely to be classified under cs.AI. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - Information extraction is closely related to information retrieval, and the paper proposes a model to extract information from text. Hence, it is likely to be classified under cs.IR. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a neural network-based approach to information extraction, which falls under the domain of neural computing. Hence, it is likely to be classified under cs.NE.
